Police seized cocaine from a fishing vessel off the Saldahna coast on Monday WESTERN CAPE - Police in the Western Cape have seized close to R600-million worth of cocaine. Ten suspects were arrested during an operation at Saldanha Bay Port, which led to the discovery of a boat filled with drugs. READ: SA police seize haul of 'miracle' anti-Covid drug Suspects have been charged with dealing in drugs and are expected to appear in court soon. The search was conducted by the organised crime narcotics unit detectives. #sapsHQ National Commissioner of the South African Police Service, General Khehla Sitole has lauded the police in Western Cape for seizing cocaine valued at over R500 million from a fishing vessel on the Saldana coast on the evening of 1 March 2021. TM pic.twitter.com/aMABtF1mNh